io.radar.sdk.model

Class RadarRoutes

  • io.radar.sdk.model.RadarRoutes

  • public class RadarRoutes

    Represents routes from an origin to a destination. For more information, see https://radar.io/documentation/api#routing.

    See Also:
    https://radar.io/documentation/api#routing

    • Constructor Detail

      • RadarRoutes

        public RadarRoutes(RadarRoute geodesic,
                   RadarRoute foot,
                   RadarRoute bike,
                   RadarRoute car)

        Represents routes from an origin to a destination. For more information, see https://radar.io/documentation/api#routing.

        Parameters:
        geodesic - The geodesic distance between the origin and destination.
        foot - The route by foot between the origin and destination. May be null if mode not specified or route unavailable.
        bike - The route by bike between the origin and destination. May be null if mode not specified or route unavailable.
        car - The route by car between the origin and destination. May be null if mode not specified or route unavailable.
        See Also:
        https://radar.io/documentation/api#routing
